<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id79a06630-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s1674"><num value="1674">§ 1674.</num><heading> Restriction on discharge from employment by reason of garnishment</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id79a06631-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s1674/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Termination of employment</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">No employer may discharge any employee by reason of the fact that his earnings have been subjected to garnishment for any one indebtedness.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id79a06632-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s1674/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Penalties</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Whoever willfully violates subsection (a) of this section shall be fined not more than $1,000, or imprisoned not more than one year, or both.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id79a06633-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/321/tIII/s304">Pub. L. 90–321, title III, § 304</ref>, <date date="1968-05-29">May 29, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/163">82 Stat. 163</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
